## Course

A Course consists of a structured sequence of instructional content and activities, designed to teach specific skills, knowledge, or competencies over a defined period. It typically encompasses multiple LessonGroupings, Lessons, and Activities, aligning with curriculum standards and intended learning objectives for a particular grade level or subject area.

### — Properties

| Property                 | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     | Type                                                                  | Cardinality |
| :----------------------- | :---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | :-------------------------------------------------------------------- | :---------- |
| **academicSubject**      | The academic subject                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            | [AcademicSubjectENUM](?tab=t.lbb5yl7ohocr#heading=h.p0d1nxoo165f)     | 0..1        |
| **audience**             | Specifies the intended audience for a learning resource, indicating who the content is designed for or most relevant to.                                                                                                                                                                        | [EducationalAudienceENUM](?tab=t.lbb5yl7ohocr#heading=h.x4xlhqskxwc9) | 1..n        |
| **author**               | The author of this content.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     | String                                                                | 1           |
| **courseCode**           | The identifier for the Course used by the course provider (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).                                                                                                                                                                                                                | String                                                                | 0..1        |
| **curriculumLabel**      | A curriculum-specific categorization of the resource. In Illustrative Mathematics, an introductory activity might have curriculumLabel: "warm-up".                                                                                                                                              | String                                                                | 0..1        |
| **dateCreated**          | The date on which the element was created                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       | Datetime                                                              | 0..1        |
| **description**          | A description of the item.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      | String                                                                | 0..1        |
| **educationalUse**       | This property classifies the resource based on whether it is used for delivering instruction or assessing student learning                                                                                                                                                                      | [EducationalUseENUM](?tab=t.lbb5yl7ohocr#heading=h.c0ogvdfs4orp)      | 0..1        |
| **gradeLevel**           | Specifies the educational grade for which the curriculum component is intended                                                                                                                                                                                                                  | Array of [GradeLevelENUM](?tab=t.lbb5yl7ohocr#heading=h.7xcld42bbfkk) | 0..n        |
| **identifier**           | The identifier of the item, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links.                                                                                                                                                                                                                    | String                                                                | 1           |
| **inLanguage**           | The language of the content.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    | [LanguageENUM](?tab=t.lbb5yl7ohocr#heading=h.vfyyjd1u51yo)            | 0..1        |
| **license**              | A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.                                                                                                                                                                                                                    | String                                                                | 1           |
| **lmsLoadingGuidance**   | Indicates the vendor’s guidance regarding whether this learning resource should be included when loading content into a Learning Management System (LMS). This property is advisory and may be overridden by local implementation policies. The value is selected from a controlled vocabulary. | [lmsLoadingGuidanceENUM](?tab=t.lbb5yl7ohocr#heading=h.1vi1slusht6g)  | 0..1        |
| **name**                 | The name of the item.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           | String                                                                | 0..1        |
| **provider**             | The service provider, service operator, or service performer                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    | String                                                                | 0..1        |
| **providerDateCreated**  | The date on which the element was created by the provider                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       | Datetime                                                              | 1           |
| **providerDateModified** | The date on which the element was updated by the provider                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       | Datetime                                                              | 1           |
| **timeRequired**         | Approximate or typical time it usually takes to work with or through the content of this work for the typical or target audience.                                                                                                                                                               | [Duration](?tab=t.lbb5yl7ohocr#heading=h.crcs42fsm7wq)                | 0..1        |

### 

### — Course relationships

A **Course** is composed of one or more **LessonGrouping**, such as modules, units, or chapters, which together represent the major subdivisions of the course’s instructional content.\
`(:Course)-[:hasPart]->(:LessonGrouping)`

A **Course** includes one or more **Material** that support instruction, such as core texts, student workbooks, teacher guides, or supplemental resources that are used throughout the course.\
`(:Course)-[:hasPart]- >(:Material)`

A **Course** is aligned to one or more **AlignmentObject**, which specify the academic standards, learning goals, or competencies that the course is intended to teach, assess, or require.\
`(:Course)-[:hasEducationalAlignment]- >(:AlignmentObject)`

A **Course** incorporates one or more **InstructionalRoutine**, which are structured, repeatable teaching strategies or patterns consistently applied across the course’s lessons or activities.\
`(:Course)-[:usesRoutine]- >(:InstructionalRoutine)`

## LessonGrouping

A LessonGrouping organizes a set of related lessons within a curriculum. The naming and level of this grouping may vary across publishers (e.g., Unit, Module, Chapter).

In Illustrative Mathematics, an introductory activity might have curriculumLabel: "warm-up".                                                                                                                                              | String                                                                | 0..1        |
| **dateCreated**          | The date on which the element was created                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       | Datetime                                                              | 0..1        |
| **description**          | A description of the item.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      | String                                                                | 0..1        |
| **educationalUse**       | This property classifies the resource based on whether it is used for delivering instruction or assessing student learning                                                                                                                                                                      | [EducationalUseENUM](?tab=t.lbb5yl7ohocr#heading=h.c0ogvdfs4orp)      | 0..1        |

### 

### — LessonGrouping Relationships

A **LessonGrouping** contains one or more **Lesson**, each representing a focused instructional session that contributes to the overall learning goals of the grouping.\
`(:LessonGrouping)-[:hasPart]->(:Lesson)`

A **LessonGrouping** may contain other **LessonGrouping** to represent nested structures (e.g., a module composed of units, or a unit composed of sections) within the curriculum.\
`(:LessonGrouping)-[:hasPart]->(:LessonGrouping)`

A **LessonGrouping** includes one or more **Material**, such as anchor texts, instructional guides, or supplemental readings, that are used throughout the grouping.\
`(:LessonGrouping)-[:hasPart]- >(:Material`)

A **LessonGrouping** is aligned to one or more **AlignmentObjects**, which specify the academic standards or competencies that the grouping is designed to teach, assess, or build toward.\
`(:LessonGrouping)-[:hasEducationalAlignment]- >(:AlignmentObject)`

A **LessonGrouping** depends on one or more other **LessonGroupings**, indicating that certain knowledge or skills must be developed beforehand to effectively engage with the current grouping.\
`(:LessonGrouping)-[:hasDependency]->(:LessonGrouping)`

## Lesson

A Lesson represents a focused instructional session within a larger curriculum structure, such as a LessonGrouping or Course, designed to achieve specific learning objectives. It typically includes activities, discussions, and assessments, and is intended to be completed within a defined timeframe, such as a class period or session.

### 

### — Relationships

A **Lesson** is composed of one or more **Activity**, which are discrete instructional tasks such as discussions, readings, hands-on work, or practice exercises that make up the lesson.\
`(:Lesson)-[:hasPart]->(:Activity)`

A **Lesson** is aligned to one or more **AlignmentObjects**, specifying the academic standards or learning goals the lesson is intended to address, assess, or build toward.\
`(:Lesson)-[:hasEducationalAlignment]- >(:AlignmentObject)`

A **Lesson** depends on one or more other **Lesson**, indicating that prerequisite content or skills must be taught before this lesson can be effectively delivered.\
`(:Lesson)-[:hasDependency]->(:Lesson)`

A **Lesson** incorporates one or more **InstructionalRoutine**, which are structured teaching practices used consistently within the lesson to support student engagement and understanding.\
`(:Lesson)-[:usesRoutine]->(:InstructionalRoutine)`

A **Lesson** uses one or more **ClassroomMaterial**, such as handouts, manipulatives, digital tools, or other tangible resources necessary for lesson delivery.\
`(:Lesson)-[:uses]->(:ClassroomMaterial)`

A **Lesson** references one or more other **Lesson**, indicating a non-sequential connection such as revisiting prior content, drawing comparisons, or reinforcing earlier concepts.\
`(:Lesson)-[:references]->(:Lesson)`

### 

### — Relationships

An **Activity** is composed of one or more **Material**, which are the instructional resources, texts, media, or tools that support the execution of the activity.

`(:Activity)-[:hasPart]->(:Material)`

An **Activity** is aligned to one or more **AlignmentObject**, specifying the academic standards or learning goals the activity is designed to address or support.

`(:Activity)-[:hasEducationalAlignment]- >(:AlignmentObject)`

An **Activity** depends on one or more other **Activity**, indicating that prior tasks or concepts must be introduced before this activity can be successfully undertaken.

`(:Activity)-[:hasDependency]->(:Activity)`

An **Activity** incorporates one or more **InstructionalRoutine**, which are recurring teaching strategies or formats that structure how the activity is conducted.

`(:Activity)-[:usesRoutine]->(:InstructionalRoutine)`

An **Activity** uses one or more **ClassroomMaterial**, such as physical objects, worksheets, or digital aids essential for completing the activity.

`(:Activity)-[:uses]->(:ClassroomMaterial)`

An **Activity** references one or more **Lesson**, drawing on prior instructional content to build connections, reinforce knowledge, or contextualize learning.

`(:Activity)-[:references]->(:Lesson)`

### — Relationships

An **Assessment** references one or more **Lesson**, indicating that the assessment draws on content, skills, or knowledge taught in those lessons.

An **Assessment** is aligned to one or more **AlignmentObject**, specifying the standards or learning objectives the assessment is designed to evaluate.

`(:Assessment)-[:hasEducationalAlignment]- >(:AlignmentObject)`

### 

### — Relationships

An **Activity** incorporates one or more **InstructionalRoutine**, which are structured teaching practices consistently used to guide student engagement and learning within the activity.

`(:Activity)-[:usesRoutine]->(:InstructionalRoutine)`
